{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"code":["🧬 Theme version: 2.5.0"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the Sosh theme any Sosh product must use, and cannot be subclassed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It embeds also in its target the Sosh brand colors which are not shared nor exposed in lower level targets or outside any module not depending to it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In other words, this ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is based on the abstract ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"text":", uses all the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange Unified Design System"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" kit and brings the Sosh brand colors and assets.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme embeds and registers the fonts for the Sosh theme, you just need to use the theme object as is."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"tip","type":"aside"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Sosh theme does not embed colors for charts yet and is read only: it cannot be subclassed or derivated"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside"},{"text":"How to use the theme","anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" directly. To use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" without further modifications, you will have to use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for your root view and give it an instance of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesSosh\/documentation\/OUDSThemesSosh\/SoshTheme","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". Keep in mind the themes are ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift class objects","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: SoshTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","        \/\/ For button configuration: theme.button","        \/\/ For link configuration: theme.link","        \/\/ Etc.","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"How to tune the theme","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-tune-the-theme"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You cannot tune the Sosh theme.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Typography","anchor":"Typography","type":"heading"